
SMTP, POP3 & IMAP
🎯 Objective

Learn how email communication works, understand the roles of SMTP, POP3, and IMAP, compare them, learn their default ports, and practice useful Linux networking commands.

📖 What is Email Communication?

When you send an email, different protocols work together:

SMTP → Sends emails.
POP3 → Downloads emails to a device.
IMAP → Synchronizes emails across multiple devices.

Think of it like a postal system:

SMTP = Sending a letter.
POP3 = Taking all letters home from the mailbox.
IMAP = Reading the same mailbox from different locations while keeping everything synchronized.

