📨 SMTP (Simple Mail Transfer Protocol)

SMTP is responsible for sending emails.

It is used:

From your email application to the mail server.
Between mail servers.
Default SMTP Ports
Port	Purpose
25	Server-to-server mail transfer
587	Secure mail submission (STARTTLS)
465	SMTP over SSL/TLS
📥 POP3 (Post Office Protocol Version 3)

POP3 is used to download emails from the mail server to your local device.

After downloading, emails are often removed from the server (depending on client settings).

POP3 Features
Downloads emails locally.
Works well without a continuous Internet connection.
Simple protocol.
Limited synchronization across multiple devices.
Default POP3 Ports
Port	Purpose
110	Standard POP3
995	POP3 over SSL/TLS
📬 IMAP (Internet Message Access Protocol)

IMAP allows email clients to synchronize emails with the server.

Emails remain on the server, making it easy to access the same mailbox from multiple devices.

IMAP Features
Emails stay on the server.
Supports multiple devices.
Synchronizes folders, read/unread status, and message organization.
Default IMAP Ports
Port	Purpose
143	Standard IMAP
993	IMAP over SSL/TLS
